eyewitness /ˈaɪˌwɪtnɪs/

(eyewitnesses) 

1. N-COUNT An eyewitness is a person who was present at an event and can therefore describe it, for example in a law court. 目击者 

例： Eyewitnesses say the police then opened fire on the crowd. 目击者说警察随即向人群开了火。

